-- SEC Said to Consider Claims Against Cohen After SAC Wells Notice
-- B y   J o s h u a   G a l l u
-- 2012-11-28T15:34:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-28/sec-said-to-consider-claims-against-cohen-after-sac-wells-notice.html
U.S. Securities and Exchange
Commission investigators are considering fraud and control-
person claims against  Steven Cohen , the billionaire founder of
SAC Capital Advisors LP, after signaling they intended to pursue
related sanctions against his firm, a person familiar with the
matter said.  Jonathan Gasthalter, a spokesman for SAC, declined to
comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joshua Gallu in Washington at 
